<h2><strong>India, land of pre-eminent biodiversity, varying landforms, rare flora &amp; fauna and spectacular view is leading tourist place in world today.</strong></h2>
Since years India has been an enticing destination for millions of exploring hearts and this is all because of rich cultural heritage of incredible India which keeps apprising people around the world about its history.

Well, if we go through speciality of Indian subcontinent then for sure you can’t take your eyes away from the beauteous grasslands, pleasant waterfalls, alluring high mountain peaks covered with snow and radiant plateaus from where this world seems to be part of your conscience.

The Indian Himalayas offer some of the most spectacular trekking experiences in the world. Here are some reasons why you should consider trekking in the Indian Himalayas:
<ol>
 	<li>Spectacular Views: The Indian Himalayas offer breathtaking views of snow-capped peaks, pristine valleys, and stunning landscapes. Trekking in the Himalayas provides an opportunity to experience nature in all its glory.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Himalayas are home to many indigenous communities that have unique customs and traditions. Trekking in the Indian Himalayas offers an opportunity to interact with the locals and learn about their way of life.</li>
 	<li>Varied Terrain: The Indian Himalayas offer a diverse range of terrain, from lush forests to high-altitude deserts. Each trek offers a unique experience, making it a popular destination for adventure enthusiasts.</li>
 	<li>Wildlife: The Indian Himalayas are home to many rare and endangered species of wildlife, including the elusive snow leopard. Trekking in the Himalayas offers an opportunity to spot these beautiful creatures in their natural habitat.</li>
 	<li>Adventure: Trekking in the Himalayas is a challenging and rewarding experience. It requires physical fitness and mental toughness, but the sense of achievement upon reaching the summit is unparalleled.</li>
 	<li>Spiritual Experience: The Himalayas are considered sacred by many religions, including Hinduism and Buddhism. Trekking in the Indian Himalayas offers an opportunity to connect with nature and experience a sense of spirituality.</li>
</ol>
In conclusion, trekking in the Indian Himalayas offers a unique and unforgettable experience that combines adventure, culture, spirituality, and natural beauty. The Indian Himalayas should be on every trekker's bucket list.
<h2><strong>India is a country with diverse terrain, ranging from the Himalayas in the north to the Western Ghats in the south. This diverse landscape offers a plethora of trekking options to adventure enthusiasts, with many treks being safe and well-marked.</strong></h2>
Here are some reasons why trekking in India can be considered safe:
<ol>
 	<li>Well-marked trails: Most of the popular trekking routes in India have well-defined trails that are easy to follow, making it easier for trekkers to navigate their way. Additionally, many treks have guides and porters who can assist trekkers in case of any difficulty.</li>
 	<li>Experienced guides: Many trekking companies in India provide experienced guides who are well-versed with the trekking route, the local flora and fauna, and the culture of the region. These guides can help ensure the safety of the trekkers and provide valuable insights into the region.</li>
 	<li>Trekking permits: In many trekking regions in India, trekking permits are required to ensure the safety of trekkers. These permits help authorities keep track of the number of trekkers on a particular trail and can assist in search and rescue operations in case of any emergency.</li>
 	<li>Safety measures: Many trekking companies in India take safety measures seriously and provide essential safety equipment such as tents, sleeping bags, first aid kits, and emergency communication devices like satellite phones.</li>
 	<li>Local support: In many trekking regions, local communities are involved in providing support to trekkers, such as homestays, food, and transport. This not only helps the local economy but also provides trekkers with a safe and authentic experience.</li>
</ol>
While trekking in India can be safe, it's essential to be well-prepared, physically fit, and follow safety guidelines. It's also crucial to respect the environment, the local culture, and the local communities while trekking.
<h2>STATES IN INDIA FAMOUS FOR TOP MOST TREKS</h2>
1. UTTRAKHAND
2. HIMACHAL PRADESH
UNION TERRITORIES, FAMOUS FOR FINEST TREKS
3. JAMMU &amp; KASHMIR
4. LADAKH
<h2>BEST TREKS IN UTTRAKHAND</h2>
If you are devotee of gods and like adventure at the same time then Uttarakhand is the perfect place to go where you experience variety of cultures. The quote ‘athithi devo bhava’means guests are like god sits perfectly the way locals treats you in Uttarakhand.

Here are some treks in Uttarakhand you must do which are placed in hierarchy of easy to moderate and moderate to hard.
<h2>Dayara Bugyal Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 05 Nights 06Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time: - All year [excluding monsoon]</li>
 	<li>Altitude: - 11,181 feet</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Easy - moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/dayara-bugyal/">Dayara Bugyal Trek</a> is one of the pre-eminent treks which are highly suitable for family, friends and school groups. This alluring trek stands in between high snow-covered peaks which consequently turns out to be the most fantastic winter trek inUttarakhand.
<h2>Kedarkantha Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 05 Nights 06Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time: - All year</li>
 	<li>Altitude: - 12,500 feet</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Easy - moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/kedarkantha/">Kedarkantha Trek</a> is considered as one of the most popular winter trek in Uttarakhand. It is best trek for beginners. The best part of this trek is to witness the sunrise from summit which is a life time experience. This trek provide the panoramic view of Himalayan Mountainsranges.
<h2>Har Ki Dun Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 06 Nights 07Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time: - All year</li>
 	<li>Altitude: - 3645 Meters</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/har-ki-dun/">Har Ki dun Trek</a> is the best trek to experience local culture in which especiallyOsla village provide a perfect scenery of life of locals their day to day activities. In this trek we move along a river Supin and terrain is very easy with slope at some places, camp sides provides views of surrounding mountains and river. You must visit this place to experience nature from close.
<h2>Chopta Tungnath &amp; Chandrashila Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 03 Nights 04Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time: - All year</li>
 	<li>Altitude: - 3680 Meters</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Easy - Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/chopta-tungnath-chandrashila-trek/">Chopta Tungnath &amp; Chandrashila Trek</a> comes under Kedarnath Musk Dear Sanctuary in Uttarakhand. This region is blessed with plentiful of wildlife, so chances are there, that you can spot wildlife including goat and Himalayan monal in morning time.
This trek takes you to the heaven itself and also popularly known as ‘Mini Switzerland’ of Uttarakhand. Choptaalso comes in the centre of Panch Kedar Trek route. If you are planning for a trek with some integration of spirituality for ultimate peace of mind then this trek should be at top in your priority list.
<h2>Rupin and Supin Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 05 Nights 06Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time: - All year</li>
 	<li>Altitude: - 3800 Meters</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Easy - Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/rupin-and-supin-trek/">Rupin and Supin Trek</a> is one of the least explored treks perhaps, a good trek for beginners. Here rush is very less so you can experience peace in isolation from worldly worries .You will also get a touch of local cultural life and Himalayan villages in this trek.It lies in the north-west corner of Uttarakhand. In this trek you will get to see Rupin River and the place where it meets Supin River and form a new river Tons. Moreover, these valleys are extremely beautiful with best scenic views. Duringthe trek, you will get the view of majestic peaks, snow covered mountains and valleys.
<h2>Valley of flowers Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 05 Nights 06Days from Haridwar to Haridwar- or Rishikesh</li>
 	<li>Best Time: - July August</li>
 	<li>Altitude: - (12,140 feet)</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/valley-of-flowers-trek/">Valley of flower Trek</a> listed in the world heritage sites in Uttarakhand Himalayas which is most popular monsoon trek. This trek is extremely vast, well furnished with never ending meadows and was declared as a national park in 1982. Valley of flower will literally rejuvenate your soul and you will reminisce about your journey.
<h2>GAUMUKH TAPOVAN TREK</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 05 Nights 06Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time: -April, May, June, September, October,</li>
 	<li>Altitude: - 13200 Feet</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/gaumukh-trek/">Gomukh TAPOVAN Trek</a> – The Holy River Ganges is the most sacred river in the Indiansubcontinent and longest river flowing in territory of India andits source is Gomukh at the Gangotri glacier.

The glacier follows Westerly route located below Chaukhamba Mountain, the highest peak of the Group.
This is the only Ganga valley from where one can see Bhagirathi peak – I, II, III, Shivling Peak and Marti Peak, Raktvan. , all together. One can also see the Tapovan and Nill Tal (4400 MT) peaks from here.
<h2>BARAADSAR LAKE TREK</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 07 Nights 08 Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time:May, June, Sep, Oct, Nov</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 4300 Meter</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/baraadsar-lake-trek/">Baraadsar Lake Trek</a> lies amidst high ridges at an altitude of 4,300 meters and is worshiped by the people. It is one of the virgin treks not known by many.

This trek come under Govind Wildlife Sanctuary National park in Uttarkashi district Uttarakhand .No doubt, the Himalayas have enchanting beauty, bracing climate and desirable soothing green meadow.

So, what else can be better than spending some days here in the serenity !
<h2>BALI PASS TREK</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 07 Nights 08 Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time: May, June, September, October, November</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 4950 m</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Difficult</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/bali-pass-trek/">Bali Pass Trek</a> lies at the height Altitude of 4953 Meters. The Bali Pass Trek starts from Sankri Base Camp, which is the base camp of more than twenty-five Treks In Uttarakhand and Ends at Trek Yamunotri Jankichatti.
The special thing is that, you can also do this trek together with Harkidoon trek, for which you must have Dehradun to Dehradun for 8 nights and 9 days. includes transport.
<h2>DODITAL TREK</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 05 Nights 06 Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time:All Year</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 3024 Meters</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/dodital-trek/">Dodital Trek</a> is the most famous trek in Uttarakhand India and Many people come from abroad to visit this place. This lake is around 1.5 km big. The Fish brought by an English trekker was released in 1971. This has now been thousands.

We can see beautiful views on the route of Dodital. A village comes after 4 km short walk, whose name is Agoda village. Agoda village is the last village of this area.
<h2><strong>Kuari Pass Trek </strong></h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 05 Nights 06 Days from Dehradun to Dehradun</li>
 	<li>Best Time: All Year</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 3650 Meters</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
Kuari Pass Trek is a popular trekking route located in the Chamoli district of Uttarakhand, India. It is a moderate-level trek and is ideal for both beginners and experienced trekkers. Here are some highlights of the Kuari Pass Trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The Kuari Pass Trek offers breathtaking views of snow-capped peaks, lush green meadows, and dense forests. Trekkers can enjoy panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Nanda Devi, Dronagiri, and Kamet.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Kuari Pass Trek offers an opportunity to interact with the local communities and experience their way of life. Trekkers can explore the local culture, cuisine, and customs of the Garhwal region.</li>
 	<li>Varied Terrain: The Kuari Pass Trek offers a diverse range of terrain, from dense forests to high-altitude meadows. The trek passes through rhododendron forests, alpine meadows, and high-altitude glaciers.</li>
 	<li>Wildlife: The Kuari Pass Trek is home to many rare and endangered species of wildlife, including the Himalayan musk deer and snow leopard. Trekkers may have the chance to spot these elusive creatures in their natural habitat.</li>
 	<li>Summit Climb: The Kuari Pass Trek offers an opportunity to climb to the summit of Kuari Pass, which is at an altitude of 3,650 meters. The climb is challenging but offers a sense of achievement upon reaching the summit.</li>
 	<li>Trekking Experience: The Kuari Pass Trek is a moderate-level trek that is ideal for both beginners and experienced trekkers. It offers an opportunity to experience trekking in the Himalayas and enjoy the beauty of nature.</li>
</ol>
In conclusion, the Kuari Pass Trek is a popular trekking route that offers a combination of scenic beauty, cultural experience, varied terrain, wildlife, and a sense of achievement upon reaching the summit. It is a must-visit destination for every trekking enthusiast
<h2><strong>Borasu Pass Trek </strong></h2>
Borasu Pass Trek is a high-altitude trek located in the Uttarkashi district of Uttarakhand, India. It is a challenging trek and is ideal for experienced trekkers who are looking for a more challenging and adventurous experience. Here are some highlights of the Borasu Pass Trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The Borasu Pass Trek offers breathtaking views of snow-capped peaks, alpine meadows, and lush green forests. Trekkers can enjoy panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Swargarohini and Banderpoonch.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Borasu Pass Trek offers an opportunity to interact with the local communities and experience their way of life. Trekkers can explore the local culture, cuisine, and customs of the Garhwal region.</li>
 	<li>Varied Terrain: The Borasu Pass Trek offers a diverse range of terrain, from dense forests to high-altitude meadows. The trek passes through oak and deodar forests, alpine meadows, and high-altitude glaciers.</li>
 	<li>Wildlife: The Borasu Pass Trek is home to many rare and endangered species of wildlife, including the Himalayan black bear and musk deer. Trekkers may have the chance to spot these elusive creatures in their natural habitat.</li>
 	<li>Challenging Summit Climb: The Borasu Pass Trek offers an opportunity to climb to the summit of Borasu Pass, which is at an altitude of 5,450 meters. The climb is challenging and requires technical expertise, but offers a sense of achievement upon reaching the summit.</li>
 	<li>Trekking Experience: The Borasu Pass Trek is a challenging trek that requires physical fitness, mental toughness, and experience in high-altitude trekking. It offers an opportunity to experience trekking in the Himalayas and enjoy the beauty of nature.</li>
</ol>
<h2><strong>Kedartal Trek </strong></h2>
Kedartal Trek is a popular high-altitude trek located in the Uttarkashi district of Uttarakhand, India. It is a moderate to difficult level trek and is ideal for both beginners and experienced trekkers. Here are some highlights of the Kedartal Trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The Kedartal Trek offers stunning views of snow-capped peaks, glaciers, and the emerald-green Kedartal Lake. Trekkers can enjoy panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Thalay Sagar, Bhrigupanth, and Jogin group of peaks.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Kedartal Trek offers an opportunity to interact with the local communities and experience their way of life. Trekkers can explore the local culture, cuisine, and customs of the Garhwal region.</li>
 	<li>Varied Terrain: The Kedartal Trek offers a diverse range of terrain, from dense forests to high-altitude meadows. The trek passes through oak and deodar forests, alpine meadows, and high-altitude glaciers.</li>
 	<li>Wildlife: The Kedartal Trek is home to many rare and endangered species of wildlife, including the Himalayan black bear and musk deer. Trekkers may have the chance to spot these elusive creatures in their natural habitat.</li>
 	<li>Summit Climb: The Kedartal Trek offers an opportunity to climb to the summit of Thalay Sagar, which is at an altitude of 6,904 meters. The climb is challenging and requires technical expertise, but offers a sense of achievement upon reaching the summit.</li>
 	<li>Trekking Experience: The Kedartal Trek is a moderate to difficult level trek that is ideal for both beginners and experienced trekkers. It offers an opportunity to experience trekking in the Himalayas and enjoy the beauty of nature.</li>
</ol>
<h2><strong>Brahmatal Trek </strong></h2>
Brahmatal Trek is a popular high-altitude trek located in the Chamoli district of Uttarakhand, India. It is a moderate level trek and is ideal for both beginners and experienced trekkers. Here are some highlights of the Brahmatal Trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The Brahmatal Trek offers stunning views of snow-capped peaks, valleys, and frozen lakes. Trekkers can enjoy panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Nanda Ghunti, Trishul, and Chaukhamba.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Brahmatal Trek offers an opportunity to interact with the local communities and experience their way of life. Trekkers can explore the local culture, cuisine, and customs of the Garhwal region.</li>
 	<li>Varied Terrain: The Brahmatal Trek offers a diverse range of terrain, from dense forests to high-altitude meadows. The trek passes through oak and rhododendron forests, alpine meadows, and high-altitude ridges.</li>
 	<li>Wildlife: The Brahmatal Trek is home to many rare and endangered species of wildlife, including the Himalayan black bear and musk deer. Trekkers may have the chance to spot these elusive creatures in their natural habitat.</li>
 	<li>Summit Climb: The Brahmatal Trek offers an opportunity to climb to the summit of Brahmatal, which is at an altitude of 3,842 meters. The climb is moderate and requires good physical fitness, but offers a sense of achievement upon reaching the summit.</li>
 	<li>Trekking Experience: The Brahmatal Trek is a moderate level trek that is ideal for both beginners and experienced trekkers. It offers an opportunity to experience trekking in the Himalayas and enjoy the beauty of nature.</li>
</ol>
<h2><strong>Rupin pass Trek </strong></h2>
Rupin Pass Trek is a popular high-altitude trek located in the Uttarkashi district of Uttarakhand, India. It is a moderate to difficult level trek and is ideal for both beginners and experienced trekkers. Here are some highlights of the Rupin Pass Trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The Rupin Pass Trek offers stunning views of snow-capped peaks, valleys, waterfalls, and meadows. Trekkers can enjoy panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Kailash, Kinnaur Kailash, and Rangrik Rang.</li>
 	<li>Varied Terrain: The Rupin Pass Trek offers a diverse range of terrain, from dense forests to high-altitude glaciers. The trek passes through oak and deodar forests, alpine meadows, and high-altitude rocky ridges.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Rupin Pass Trek offers an opportunity to interact with the local communities and experience their way of life. Trekkers can explore the local culture, cuisine, and customs of the Kinnaur region.</li>
 	<li>Waterfalls: The Rupin Pass Trek is known for its spectacular waterfalls, including the Rupin waterfall, which is one of the highest waterfalls in India.</li>
 	<li>Summit Climb: The Rupin Pass Trek offers an opportunity to climb to the summit of Rupin Pass, which is at an altitude of 4,650 meters. The climb is challenging and requires good physical fitness and trekking experience.</li>
 	<li>Trekking Experience: The Rupin Pass Trek is a moderate to difficult level trek that is ideal for both beginners and experienced trekkers. It offers an opportunity to experience trekking in the Himalayas and enjoy the beauty of nature.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Adi Kailash or Om Parvat Trek</h2>
Adi Kailash or Om Parvat Trek is a challenging trek located in the Pithoragarh district of Uttarakhand, India. It is a high-altitude trek that takes you to the sacred site of Adi Kailash, which is believed to be the original abode of Lord Shiva. Here are some highlights of the Adi Kailash Om Parvat Trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The Adi Kailash Om Parvat Trek offers stunning views of snow-capped peaks, valleys, and forests. Trekkers can enjoy panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Nanda Devi, Nanda Kot, and Panchchuli.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Adi Kailash Om Parvat Trek offers an opportunity to interact with the local communities and experience their way of life. Trekkers can explore the local culture, cuisine, and customs of the Bhotia people.</li>
 	<li>Varied Terrain: The Adi Kailash Om Parvat Trek offers a diverse range of terrain, from dense forests to high-altitude rocky ridges. The trek passes through oak and rhododendron forests, alpine meadows, and high-altitude glaciers.</li>
 	<li>Summit Climb: The Adi Kailash Om Parvat Trek offers an opportunity to climb to the summit of Adi Kailash, which is at an altitude of 6,191 meters. The climb is challenging and requires good physical fitness and mountaineering experience.</li>
 	<li>Sacred Site: Adi Kailash is a sacred site for Hindus and is believed to be the original abode of Lord Shiva. The trek offers an opportunity to visit this holy site and experience the spiritual energy of the place.</li>
 	<li>Trekking Experience: The Adi Kailash Om Parvat Trek is a challenging trek that is ideal for experienced trekkers who are looking for a unique and spiritual trekking experience.</li>
</ol>
