<h2>BEST TREKS IN HIMACHAL PRADESH</h2>
<h2>Hampta Pass Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 04 Nights 05 Days from</li>
 	<li>Best Time: May to October</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 4200 Metres</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
The name ‘Hampta Pass’derived from Hampta village. This trek is located in Pir Panjal range and it is the passage between Lahaul and Kullu, or Manali valley of Himachal Pradesh.

<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/hampta-pass/">Hampta Pass Trek</a>, known today is the most popular trek not in India but all over the world that is why thousands of people come here every year in months of July and August.This trek is also special as it starts from Manali, the beautiful city of Himachal Pradesh.
<h2>Sar Pass Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 04 Nights 05 Days from Kullu to Kullu</li>
 	<li>Best Time:May to October</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 4200 Metres</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/sar-pass-trek/">Sar Pass Trek</a> is a stunning trek from Grahan village ending in Barsheini in Kullu Valley. The trek is recommended for all those who love adventure, snowy landscapes, and high mountains.

The total trek distance is 48 km. Once you reach the PASS almost close to 14,000ft, the view from the PASS is absolutely breath-taking because of the majestic mountains of Parvati Valley.

The trek starts from Kasol where you will PASS through pine forests, magnificent meadows, snow-capped mountains and some of the most jaw-dropping landscapes which make SAR Pass one of the best treks for beginners
<h2>BURAN GHATI TREK</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 06Nights 07Days from Shimla to Shimla</li>
 	<li>Best Time: May June September October</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 4572 meter</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/buran-ghati/">Buran Ghati Trek</a> is a highly diverse trek and a thrilling pass that lies in the heart of Himachal Pradesh. The special stop of this trek is Chandranahan Lake, a beautiful lake in the middle of hills.

Another speciality of this trek is that it starts from Janglik villageand ends at Barua road head, due to which you are not going to feel the same anywhere throughout the trek, every day you will wake up with new scenario which would be enough to take your breath away.
<h2>Chandranahan Lake Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 05 Nights 06 Days from Kullu to Kullu</li>
 	<li>Best Time: MayJune September October</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 13900feet</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Easy to Moderate</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/chandranahan-lake/">Chandranahan Lake</a> is best trekking place in Himachal Pradesh. This is small lake which attracts a lot of people to visit here once in a lifetime. This trek surrounds undulating meadows that remain covered in snow during winters and dense forest which further leads to the BuranGhati Pass.

The trek of Chandranahan lake starts from a quaint village called Janglik village.This trek exposes the landscape similar to Switzerland and Alps.
<h2><strong>Spiti Valley Trek </strong></h2>
The Spiti Valley Trek is a high altitude trek that takes you through the beautiful Spiti Valley in the Indian state of Himachal Pradesh. Here are some highlights of the trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The Spiti Valley Trek offers stunning views of the snow-capped Himalayan peaks, beautiful valleys, and the Spiti River. The trek takes you through the picturesque villages of Kibber, Komic, and Langza, which are located at high altitudes and offer a unique insight into the local way of life.</li>
 	<li>Challenging Terrain: The Spiti Valley Trek is a challenging trek that requires a good level of fitness and prior trekking experience. The trek involves crossing several high altitude passes, including the Kunzum La Pass and the Parang La Pass, which are located at an altitude of over 5,000 meters.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Spiti Valley is known for its rich Buddhist culture and traditions. The trek takes you through several ancient monasteries, including the Key Monastery and the Tabo Monastery, which are over 1000 years old and offer a glimpse into the region's cultural heritage.</li>
 	<li>Wildlife: The Spiti Valley is home to a variety of wildlife, including the elusive snow leopard, Himalayan ibex, and blue sheep. The trek offers an opportunity to spot these animals in their natural habitat.</li>
 	<li>Weather: The best time to do the Spiti Valley Trek is from June to September when the weather is pleasant and the skies are clear. The region experiences harsh winter conditions, and the trek is closed during the winter months.</li>
</ol>
In conclusion, the Spiti Valley Trek is a beautiful trek that offers a combination of scenic beauty, cultural experience, and a sense of adventure. It is a must-do trek for every trekking enthusiast who wishes to explore the hidden treasures of the Himalayas.
<h2>Kanamo Peak Trek</h2>
The Kanamo Peak Trek is a popular trekking destination located in the Spiti Valley of Himachal Pradesh in India. Here are some highlights of the trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Summiting Kanamo Peak: The highlight of the trek is summiting the Kanamo Peak, which is located at an altitude of 19,600 feet. The climb to the summit is challenging but offers breathtaking views of the surrounding mountains and valleys.</li>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The trek takes you through some of the most beautiful landscapes of the Spiti Valley, including the picturesque village of Kibber, the Chandratal Lake, and the Parang La Pass. The region is known for its stark and rugged beauty, with snow-capped peaks, barren valleys, and crystal-clear lakes.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Spiti Valley is home to a unique Tibetan culture, and the trek takes you through several ancient monasteries, including the Key Monastery and the Komic Monastery. You also get to interact with the local villagers and learn about their way of life.</li>
 	<li>Wildlife: The Spiti Valley is home to a variety of wildlife, including the elusive snow leopard, Himalayan ibex, and blue sheep. The trek offers an opportunity to spot these animals in their natural habitat.</li>
 	<li>Weather: The best time to do the Kanamo Peak Trek is from June to September when the weather is pleasant and the skies are clear. The region experiences harsh winter conditions, and the trek is closed during the winter months.</li>
</ol>
In conclusion, the Kanamo Peak Trek is a challenging and rewarding trek that offers a combination of scenic beauty, cultural experience, and a sense of adventure. It is a must-do trek for every trekking enthusiast who wishes to explore the hidden treasures of the Himalayas.
