</ol>
<h2>Bhrigu lake trek</h2>
The Bhrigu Lake Trek is a popular high-altitude trek located in the Kullu district of Himachal Pradesh in India. Here are some highlights of the trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Bhrigu Lake: The highlight of the trek is the Bhrigu Lake, which is located at an altitude of 14,100 feet. The lake is named after the sage Bhrigu, who is said to have meditated here. The lake is surrounded by snow-capped peaks, and the crystal clear waters reflect the sky, creating a stunning visual spectacle.</li>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The trek takes you through some of the most beautiful landscapes of the Kullu region, including lush green forests, high-altitude meadows, and snow-capped peaks. The region is known for its rugged beauty, with deep gorges, fast-flowing rivers, and rocky terrain.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Kullu region is home to a unique culture, and the trek takes you through several ancient villages, including Gulaba, Rola Kholi, and Pandu Ropa. You also get to interact with the local villagers and learn about their way of life.</li>
 	<li>Weather: The best time to do the Bhrigu Lake Trek is from May to November when the weather is pleasant and the skies are clear. The region experiences harsh winter conditions, and the trek is closed during the winter months.</li>
 	<li>Easy to Moderate Trek: The Bhrigu Lake Trek is an easy to moderate level trek, making it suitable for beginners as well as experienced trekkers. The trek is around 20 km long and can be completed in 3-4 days.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Deo tibba base camp trek</h2>
The Deo Tibba Base Camp Trek is a popular high-altitude trek located in the Kullu district of Himachal Pradesh in India. Here are some highlights of the trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Deo Tibba Peak: The highlight of the trek is the Deo Tibba peak, which is located at an altitude of 19,688 feet. The peak is named after the local deity, and the trek takes you to the base of the peak, offering stunning views of the surrounding peaks.</li>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The trek takes you through some of the most beautiful landscapes of the Kullu region, including lush green forests, high-altitude meadows, and snow-capped peaks. The region is known for its rugged beauty, with deep gorges, fast-flowing rivers, and rocky terrain.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The Kullu region is home to a unique culture, and the trek takes you through several ancient villages, including Jagatsukh, Pandu Ropa, and Khanol. You also get to interact with the local villagers and learn about their way of life.</li>
 	<li>Weather: The best time to do the Deo Tibba Base Camp Trek is from May to November when the weather is pleasant and the skies are clear. The region experiences harsh winter conditions, and the trek is closed during the winter months.</li>
 	<li>Moderate to Difficult Trek: The Deo Tibba Base Camp Trek is a moderate to difficult level trek, making it suitable for experienced trekkers. The trek is around 50 km long and can be completed in 6-7 days.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Pin parvati pass trek</h2>
The Pin Parvati Pass Trek is a challenging high-altitude trek that takes you through some of the most beautiful landscapes of Himachal Pradesh in India. Here are some highlights of the trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Pin Parvati Pass: The highlight of the trek is the Pin Parvati Pass, which is located at an altitude of 17,457 feet. The pass connects the lush green Parvati Valley to the barren and rugged Pin Valley, offering stunning views of the surrounding peaks.</li>
 	<li>Scenic Beauty: The trek takes you through some of the most beautiful landscapes of the region, including dense forests, high-altitude meadows, and snow-capped peaks. You also get to cross several streams, waterfalls, and glaciers along the way.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The trek takes you through several ancient villages, including Kheerganga, Tunda Bhuj, and Thakur Kuan, where you get to interact with the local villagers and learn about their way of life.</li>
 	<li>Weather: The best time to do the Pin Parvati Pass Trek is from June to September when the weather is pleasant and the skies are clear. The region experiences harsh winter conditions, and the trek is closed during the winter months.</li>
 	<li>Challenging Trek: The Pin Parvati Pass Trek is a challenging trek that requires prior experience and good physical fitness. The trek is around 110 km long and can be completed in 10-12 days.</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;
<h2>BEST TREKS IN JAMMU &amp; KASHMIR</h2>
<h3>Tarsar Marsar Trek</h3>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 06 Nights 07 Days</li>
 	<li>Best Time:July, August September</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 13205 feet</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
Kashmir, which is simply known as ‘paradise on earth’ is well-known destination for tourist all around the globe.
This trek is one of the highly opted treks of the Kashmir valley, <a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/tarsar-marsar-trek/">Tarsar Marsar Trek</a> is not only a famous trekking adventure but also a spectrum of rich vegetation in lap of snowy mountains. This trek is a moderate level trek accompanied with majestic pathways covering picturesque base camp village of Aru and three snow-capped lakes- Tarsar, Marsar &amp; Sundersar that complement each other’s perfection.
<h3>Kashmir Great Lake Trek</h3>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 06 Nights 07 Days</li>
 	<li>Best Time:July, August September</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 13850 feet</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
The <a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/kashmir-great-lakes-trek/">Kashmir Great Lake</a> is a spectacular collection of five alpine lakes spread across different valley. This trek leaves a permanent footprint in conscience of the visitors.

This seemingly astonishing and unspoiled beauty of Kashmir’s great lake is a visual feast for everyone who for some reason considers nature to be the best painter known to mankind.

This trek has proven ultimate blessing of nature since years because of the positive spiritual vibes which can be felt here, as one can heal his all pain &amp; darkness in lap of peaceful aura.
<h2>Naranag Mahlish Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 03Nights 04 Days</li>
 	<li>Best Time:JULY TO OCT</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 3575 M</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Moderate</li>
</ul>
The <a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/naranag-gangabal-trek/">Narang Mahlisa Trek</a> is travel friendly trek which shows the natural simplicity of Jammu &amp; Kashmir valley.

This trek really do justice with the glorification of Kashmir valley as simply heaven on earth, a tranquil environment with an unbroken view of star-studded sky is a prize worth seeking out. This region converts into a snow walk in April-May &amp; October- November, providing a stunning view of Himalayas.
<h2>Nafran Valley Trek kashmir</h2>
The Nafran Valley Trek is a relatively unknown but beautiful trek that takes you through the scenic landscapes of Kashmir in northern India. Here are some highlights of the trek:
<ol>
 	<li>Natural Beauty: The trek takes you through the stunning landscapes of the Nafran Valley, which is known for its lush green forests, high-altitude meadows, and snow-capped peaks. You will also get to see several streams and waterfalls along the way.</li>
 	<li>Cultural Experience: The trek takes you through several small villages in the region where you get to interact with the locals and learn about their way of life. The people of the region are warm and welcoming, and you will get to taste some of the delicious local cuisines.</li>
 	<li>Moderate Trek: The Nafran Valley Trek is a moderate trek that can be completed in 5-6 days. The trek covers a distance of around 50 km and is suitable for both beginners and experienced trekkers.</li>
 	<li>Weather: The best time to do the Nafran Valley Trek is from June to September when the weather is pleasant and the skies are clear. The region experiences heavy snowfall during the winter months, and the trek is closed during this time.</li>
 	<li>Offbeat Trek: The Nafran Valley Trek is a relatively unknown trek and sees very few trekkers. If you are looking for an offbeat trekking experience, then this is the perfect trek for you.</li>
</ol>
<h2>BEST TREKS IN LADAKH</h2>
<h2>Chadar Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 07 Nights 08 Days From Leh To Leh</li>
 	<li>Best Time:Jan, Feb</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 11400 feet</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Difficult</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/chadar-trek/">Chadar Trek</a> is also known as ‘The Frozen River trek’ which basically starts from the beautiful town of Leh. This trek gives a thrilling experience to the trekkers as this trek is over a frozen river in Zanskar region of Ladakh &amp; also in this way this trek is different from all other treks.

Here the snow resemble as a thick sheet genteelly covering whole region that is why this region came to be known as Chadar.
<h2>Stok Kangri Trek</h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Duration: - 07Nights 08Days</li>
 	<li>Best Time:July, August</li>
 	<li>Altitude: 6153 Meter</li>
 	<li>Difficulty level: - Difficult</li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/stok-kangri-trek/">Stock Kangri Trek</a> is top most expedition in the Leh-Ladakh, high peaks all around with desertedlandscape makes this place much more fascinating.

The starting point of Stok Kangri Trek is Leh, which is worldwide famous for its fantastic view &amp; alluring scenery
This trek provide you most beautiful experience that you may not have ever before in your life. Well, talking about the summit view then you must know that standing at your destination would for sure make you feel like all your journey is worthy. Coming across last summit ridge witness the best view of Karakoram Range, Zansker &amp; Sansker Kangri.
<h2>BEST TREKS IN SIKKIM</h2>
Sikkim, the beautiful northeastern state of India, offers some of the most scenic and adventurous treks in the country. Here are some of the best treks in Sikkim:
<ol>
 	<li>Goecha La Trek: This is one of the most popular treks in Sikkim, and it takes you to the base of the mighty Kanchenjunga peak, the third-highest mountain in the world. The trek covers a distance of around 90 km and takes around 10-12 days to complete.</li>
 	<li>Singalila Ridge Trek: The Singalila Ridge Trek takes you through the beautiful landscapes of Sikkim and West Bengal, and offers breathtaking views of the Himalayan range. The trek covers a distance of around 80 km and takes around 7-8 days to complete.</li>
 	<li>Green Lake Trek: This is a challenging trek that takes you to the beautiful Green Lake, located at the base of Kanchenjunga. The trek covers a distance of around 90 km and takes around 10-12 days to complete.</li>
 	<li>Dzongri Trek: The Dzongri Trek takes you through the beautiful landscapes of the Khangchendzonga National Park, and offers stunning views of the Kanchenjunga peak. The trek covers a distance of around 50 km and takes around 6-7 days to complete.</li>
 	<li>Kasturi Orar Trek: This is an offbeat trek that takes you through the remote villages and beautiful landscapes of Sikkim. The trek covers a distance of around 50 km and takes around 5-6 days to complete.</li>
 	<li>Sandakphu Trek: is a popular trek in the Indian state of West Bengal, which offers breathtaking views of some of the highest peaks in the world, including Mount Everest, Kanchenjunga, Lhotse, and Makalu. The trek starts from the village of Manebhanjang, which is located at an altitude of 6,400 feet, and takes you to the Sandakphu peak, which is located at an altitude of 11,941 feet.The trek covers a distance of around 47 km and takes around 6-7 days to complete. The trail takes you through beautiful rhododendron forests, charming villages, and scenic landscapes, and offers a unique opportunity to witness the cultural and natural beauty of the region.</li>
</ol>
